{
  "narration": "Stepping softly into the Lord's Study, you scan the room for any sign of Elen. The dim candlelight flickers over shelves of ancient books and scattered parchment, casting long, uncertain shadows across the faded rug. You notice a pair of muddy bootprints--smaller and lighter than your own--leading behind the desk and around a toppled chair. A faint smear of blood mars the edge of the writing table, confirming that Elen, wounded but determined, made her way through here.\n\nAs you circle the desk, you spot a half-eaten emergency ration--standard scout issue--tucked behind a folio of maps. A scrap of blue cloth, torn but familiar, catches on a drawer handle. The air near the far bookshelf feels colder, prickling the hairs on your neck, and a faint, sorrowful whisper rises--a warning or plea, its words just beyond recognition.\n\nYou can press your search for further clues, call out to Elen, or investigate the unnaturally cold bookshelf. But be wary--the study is thick with enchantments, and disturbing the wrong book or artifact could trigger the animated defenses that guard these secrets.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updatePlot",
      "parameters": {
        "plotPointId": "PP003",
        "newStatus": "in progress",
        "plotImpact": "Norn has found clear evidence of Elen's passage and injury in the Lord's Study--her bootprints, a blood smear, an emergency ration, and a torn scrap of cloak. The cold, whispering presence and the enchanted bookshelves suggest more secrets and danger ahead."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You take a steadying breath and call out, your voice echoing softly through the Lord's Study. \"Elen! It's Norn! If you're here, show yourself. You're safe--or as safe as you can be.\"\n\nThe flicker of candlelight shudders, and for a heartbeat, the sorrowful whispers in the air intensify. From behind the desk, the faintest scuff of movement answers you--but not Elen's comforting reply. Instead, a cold, weighty presence settles behind you, and the noble portrait above the mantle seems to darken, the painted eyes narrowing as shadows slide from its edges to coalesce into a looming, armored figure: the Shadow of Sir Garran.\n\nHis form wavers between man and living darkness, spectral blade in hand, voice like wind through a tomb: \"You seek the lost, yet trespass deeper still. Her blood stains these stones... none may disturb what I failed to protect.\"\n\nThe air grows icy. Tomes along the shelf quiver, and the arcane circle carved into the floor pulses ominously. Something ancient and tragic animates the room--and you sense the true threat has awakened. Prepare yourself, Norn, for the Shadow of Sir Garran brooks no intrusion in this sanctum.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "createEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "player": "Norn",
        "npcs": [],
        "monsters": ["Shadow of Sir Garran"],
        "encounterSummary": "Norn's call for Elen in the Lord's Study has awakened the Shadow of Sir Garran, who manifests as a spectral guardian determined to prevent further intrusion. The room's arcane defenses stir, and combat is imminent."
      }
    }
  ]
}

Combat Summary: {
  "narration": "In the shadowed private study of Sir Garran Vael, Norn faced the fearsome Shadow of Sir Garran, a spectral guardian wielding a malevolent blade. The battle began with the ghostly knight attacking, but Norn's wards and armor thwarted each deadly strike. Seizing the opportunity, Norn unleashed a devastating counterattack, scoring multiple critical hits and inflicting heavy damage. Despite the shadow's relentless assaults, including a chilling touch that dealt cold damage to Norn, the fighter's resilience and precise strikes wore down the foe. In the second round, Norn's focused attacks culminated in the Shadow's dissolution, ending the spectral threat and restoring a fragile calm to the arcane-laden chamber. With the Shadow of Sir Garran defeated, Norn earned 2900 experience points for the victory.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "LordStudyCombat",
        "changes": "Shadow of Sir Garran takes 72 damage, HP reduced from 90 to 18 after first round; further 19 damage in second round reduces HP from 18 to 0, Shadow defeated and dissipated."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "HP reduced from 18 to 13 due to 5 cold damage from Shadow's chilling touch; healed earlier with Second Wind to 18 HP; status alive, condition none."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "exit"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "As the echoes of battle fade from the Lord's Study, you catch your breath amidst the settling shadows. The arcane containment circle stops glowing, and the oppressive cold lifts, leaving the chamber heavy with silence and sorrow. The Shadow of Sir Garran dissipates like morning mist, only a fading echo of his voice lingering: \"Remember... the heart... seek the key... beneath the shadow...\"\n\nYou feel the weight of the clash settle in your bones but also the unmistakable surge of victory hard-won. In the aftermath, you spot the glint of a fallen iron key amidst the scuffed rug, and a battered leather journal lying open on the desk, its final entries still legible. A locked trapdoor beneath the rug seems less concealed now, as if the study itself were urging you onward.\n\nThough battered, you stand triumphant--one step closer to Elen's fate and the truth within Shadowfall Keep.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Gained 2900 experience points for defeating the Shadow of Sir Garran. Total XP is now 10871/14000."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You kneel amid the spent magic and scattered parchments, fingers closing around the ornate iron key that once gleamed in the Shadow's spectral hand. Its black gems seem to drink in what little light remains, cold and heavy with purpose. As you slip it into your pack, you sense its significance--this is the key to something sealed far beneath the study, just as the echo of Sir Garran's warning implied.\n\nYour hand lingers on the battered leather journal, the pages curling with age and sorrow. The ink, astonishingly fresh, details Sir Garran's desperate struggle: his efforts to resist the relic's corruption and instructions for a failsafe should the darkness ever claim him. There are diagrams of the arcane circle, a map sketching a hidden chamber below, and a half-written plea for forgiveness to 'my beloved Elara.'\n\nAs you secure both items, the study feels subtly less oppressive, as if the room itself acknowledges your progress. Yet a ripple stirs along the bookshelves--animated defenses hungry for motion. What will you do next? Search further, inspect the hidden trapdoor beneath the rug, or retreat to safety before testing the limits of these lingering wards?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Added 'Ornate iron dungeon key (with shadow-absorbing gems)' to inventory. Added 'Sir Garran's leather journal (details his corruption, arcane circle, hidden chamber, and letter to Elara)' to inventory."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updatePlot",
      "parameters": {
        "plotPointId": "PP003",
        "newStatus": "in progress",
        "plotImpact": "Norn has claimed Sir Garran's journal and the ornate dungeon key, uncovering crucial clues about the source of the curse, the containment ritual, and a hidden chamber below the study."
      }
    }
  ]
}
